%e A342818 For n = 3, we have t(45) = t(48) = t(51) = t(54) = t(57) = t(60) = t(63) = t(66), and no k and m>8 exist such that t(k) = t(k+3) = t(k+2*3) = ... = t(k+(m-1)*3). So a(3)=8.
%Y A342818 Cf. A010060. Starting position of the first occurrence of a monochromatic arithmetic progression of difference n and length a(n) is given by A342827.
